<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-08-26T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-08-26T17:00:00-05:00" n="542" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d542">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">825.516/223: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CWS1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-26T18:00:00-04:00">August 26,
                                    1932—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>72. Your 178, August 20, 1 p.m. Ascertain and report by cable whether
                            reply from the Minister for Foreign Affairs concerning constitutional
                            guarantees regarding compensation refer to Article 10, Section 10 of
                            Constitution. If not, to what provision? Also ascertain what laws
                            providing compensation were referred to.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_CWR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>